# .windsurfrules — sdlc-mcp context

## Project

Foundational SDLC MCP repository. Tools, commands, and knowledge base for AI-assisted software development across the full lifecycle.

## Cross-session continuity

At session start: call `sdlc-gitmcp` to read current repo state (`sdlc/overview.md`, `docs/`). Surface what's in progress and ask where to pick up. At session end: commit updated docs so the next session — in any tool — can find them.

## Tools (always on)

- **sdlc-gitmcp**: GitMCP live read of this repo. Use at session start.
- **context7**: current library/framework docs

## Tool: Context7 (always on)

Call Context7 automatically whenever a library or framework is mentioned. Never answer package-API questions from training memory alone.

## Commands

- `/generate_prd` — PRD scaffold
- `/plan_sprint` — sprint plan
- `/create_adr` — Architecture Decision Record
- `/gen_test_plan` — test plan
- `/release_notes` — from git log

## Knowledge base

`sdlc/` folder is the source of truth for all standards and templates. Consult it before generating code, docs, or process guidance.

## Stack + conventions

- TypeScript, ESM, Node 18+
- Conventional commits
- Feature branches off `main`
- Never push directly to `main`

## Config

Only edit `config/config-sources.json`. Run `npm run sync:configs` to push changes to all tool configs.
